This paper investigates the use of associative information in reference games, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses optimal experiment design techniques to compare different models, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper's investigation of pragmatic behavior may also relate to the subfield of computational cognition (cs.CC) and the use of game theory (cs.SI).
